# Risk Prevention

| Risk | Prevention |
|------|------------|
| High Cost | Correct processor selection |
| Scaling Issues | ASG for stateless tiers |
| Compatibility Problems | Intel only where required |
| Cluster Instability | Manual provisioning for stateful services |

---

# Recommended Architecture

```text
Stateless Workloads -> ASG + Graviton
Stateful Workloads  -> Manual + AMD
Legacy Apps         -> Intel when required
```

---

# Best Practices

## Auto Scaling
Use:

- Launch Templates  
- Health Checks  
- CPU based scaling  
- Multi-AZ deployment  

---

## Processor Selection Rules

Choose Graviton for:
- Cloud native workloads
- Containers
- Cost optimization

Choose AMD for:
- Databases
- Middleware
- General x86 workloads

Choose Intel for:
- Legacy software
- Vendor constraints

---

# Final Recommendation

| Area | Recommendation |
|------|----------------|
| Stateless Layers | ASG + Graviton |
| Stateful Layers | Manual + AMD |
| Legacy Workloads | Intel only |
| Scaling Strategy | Hybrid Model |

Benefits:

- Better scalability  
- Lower cost  
- Reduced maintenance risk  
- Better performance  
- Future proof architecture  

